cwe_description: The software reads data past the end, or before the beginning, of the intended buffer. This can lead to crashes, information disclosure, or other undefined behavior.
explanation: The code accesses args[0] and args[1] without explicitly checking if the 'args' array or container has at least two elements. If 'args' contains fewer than two elements, these accesses will result in an out-of-bounds read, leading to undefined behavior such as crashes, data corruption, or information disclosure.
